====Usage notes====
The perfective form is {{ja-r|でした}}, volitional {{ja-r|でしょう}}, conjunctive {{ja-r|でして}}. Other forms are not used.

Replaces {{ja-r|だ}} in cases of nouns and adjectives which it is used with, e.g. {{m|ja|[[犬]]だ|tr=inu da||it's a dog|pos=plain}} becomes {{m|ja||犬です|tr=inu desu|pos=polite}} and {{m|ja|[[綺麗]]だ|tr=kirei da||it's pretty|pos=plain}} becomes {{m|ja||綺麗です|tr=kirei desu|pos=polite}}. Similarly, {{ja-r|でしょう}} replaces {{ja-r|だろう}} and {{ja-r|でして}} replaces {{ja-r|で}}.

{{ja-r|です}} attaches as-is to adjectives used without {{ja-r|だ}}, e.g. {{m|ja|美しい|tr=utsukushii||it is beautiful|pos=plain}} becomes {{m|ja||美しいです|tr=utsukushii desu|it is beautiful|pos=polite}} and {{m|ja|美しかった|tr=utsukushikatta||it was beautiful|pos=plain}} becomes {{m|ja||美しかったです|tr=utsukushikatta desu|it was beautiful|pos=polite}}. Forms such as {{m|ja||美しいでした}} and {{m|ja||美しいでして}} are nonstandard. For the forms {{ja-r|[[ない]] [[です]]}} and {{ja-r|[[なかった]] [[です]]}}, there are synonyms {{ja-r|ありません}} and {{ja-r|[[ありません]] [[でした]]}}. It can also be used to ask questions; {{m|ja|[[本]][[です]][[か]]|tr=hon desu ka}} means "Is this a book?"

This word is phonologically an [[enclitic]], similar to [[particle]]s. It is classified as {{m|ja|助動詞|tr=jodōshi||auxiliary verb}} in traditional Japanese grammar.

